Package networkHandler

Class GraphHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • networkHandler.GraphHandler
  • public class GraphHandler
extends java.lang.Object

    This class is responsible for managing all from GraphProperty derived classes and initiates their calculation on a Graph, which is handled in this class as well.

    It is also responsible for forwarding calls to the printing methods of the GraphProperties and calls to their value getters.

    To determine the necessary calculations it checks the flags provided by a CommandLineReader accordingly.

    Author:
    Fabian Grun, Khalid Butt
    See Also:
    BetweennessCentralityMeasure, BetweennessCentralityMeasureList, Connectivity, Diameter, GraphProperty, MinimumSpanningTree, ShortestPathList

    • Method Detail

      • runCalculations

        public void runCalculations()

        This method is responsible for handling all calculations.

        First it checks the flags provided by the commandLineReader and determines, which calculations are expected and also which might be dependent on others.

        In case a flag for file creation is set, all properties are calculated, otherwise only those specified by the printing flags of the CommandLineReader.

        Each GraphProperty is then calculated in its own Thread for efficiency, while making sure, dependencies are finished with their calculations before continuing to dependents.
